===Etymology===
Origin uncertain; according to the ''{{w|Oxford English Dictionary}}'', possibly from dialectal {{der|en|de|Christkindl}}, {{m|de|Christkindle||the [[Christ child]], believed to [[deliver]] [[present#Noun|presents]] to [[children]] on [[Christmas Eve]]; the presents so brought}}, from {{m|de|Christ||[[Christ]]}} + {{m|de|Kindl}}, {{m|de|Kindle}} (dialectal [[diminutive]] of {{m|de|Kind||[[child]]}}). The ''-ingle'' portion of the word may be a corruption of {{m|en|Kris Kringle||[[Santa Claus]]}} (also derived from {{etyl|de|-}} {{m|de|Christkindl}}, {{m|de|[[Christ]] [[Kinde]]}}) among the German community in the United States.<ref>{{R:OED Online|title=Christingle|code=32472|part of speech=n|date=1989}}</ref>

